Virginia Tracy https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Virginia_Tracy 0 Virginia Tracy (1874–1946) was an American adventurer, stage actress, novelist and screenwriter. She was the daughter of the Victorian actress Helen Tracy (1850–1924).At 20, in 1894, she wrote one of her first professional reports after accompanying a caravan of actors led by Maurice Barrymore traveling cross country on train. In the 1920s she wrote several large scale epics for the Fox Film Corporation. Virginia_Tracy ( 1874 – 1946 ) was an_American_adventurer , stage_actress , novelist_and_screenwriter .
